               <p>"27th of December, 1817.</p>
               <p>"7lbs. of white pepper, "R. STERRY and Co." by which I understood that he came from Sterry and Co. for 7lbs. of pepper for them. I gave it to him, and he took it away. I asked him his name - He said it was Clarke. I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM FAULKNER. I am warehouseman to 
               <persName id="t18180114-92-person731">R. </persName>
            Sterry and Co. The prisoner formerly lived servant with them, and was discharged in 1816-the order is his hand-writing, and is not their order.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I have nothing to say.</p>

